e\nsimilar to the ``satellite clouds'' of classic strong MgII absorbers, so this\ncould be a high-velocity cloud in the galaxy group responsible for the systems,\npossibly related to a 0.2L^* galaxy at an impact parameter of 43h^-1 kpc.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 5 Mar 2003 00:03:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-07"}
